President Biden has announced that Shuwanza Goff will be the new Director of Legislative Affairs and Assistant to the President. Goff, who has served as Deputy Director of White House Legislative Affairs and House Liaison, played a crucial role in passing significant legislation such as the American Rescue Plan and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Bill. She has strong relationships with lawmakers on both sides of the aisle and is the first African-American woman to hold this position. Goff has extensive experience in legislative operations and has previously served as the floor director for the U.S. House of Representatives. She holds a Master's degree in justice, law, and society from American University and a Bachelor's degree in political science from the University of Tennessee.